BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ucdavis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/workshop-publish-your-work"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:From Idea to Impact: Publish Your Work — Traditional and Alterna
 tive Options
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T210000
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52322769236438
DESCRIPTION:Publish Your Work: From Idea to Impact\, Traditional and Alter
 native Options is a Zoom workshop that will give you an overview of (1) tr
 aditional publishing options\, such as peer-reviewed journals\, and (2) al
 ternative publishing options\, such as preprints\, open methods\, and open
  data.\n\nWhether you’re going to be publishing for the first time or yo
 u’ve published many times in the past\, join us to learn more about open
  research\, avoiding predatory publishers\, selecting an appropriate journ
 al\, and how to publish your research outputs in ways that go beyond the t
 raditional journal article.\n \n\nNo previous experience is required. All 
 disciplines are welcome.\n\nPlease register for the Zoom link. \n\nThis si
 x-workshop series is a collaboration between the library's Scholarly Commu
 nications Program\, the Researcher Services department\, and Blaisdell Med
 ical Library. For any questions\, please contact the Scholarly Communicati
 on Officer Michael Ladisch (mladisch@ucdavis.edu). Check our events calend
 ar for more publishing workshops.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/workshop-publish-your-work
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
