BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ucdavis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/navigating-data-management-for-publication"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:From Idea to Impact: Publishing Your Work — Navigating Data Mana
 gement for Publication
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260430T210000
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52332265055740
DESCRIPTION:This workshop is targeted toward scholars\, researchers\, and 
 graduate students who are interested in the role of data management during
  the publication process. Managing your data effectively is a crucial part
  of research and scholarly communication. This session will provide founda
 tional skills for handling data throughout your project's lifecycle\, from
  planning for funder requirements to ensuring long-term reproducibility.\n
  \n\nAfter this workshop\, learners should be able to:\n \n\nUnderstand an
 d navigate funder requirements for data management and sharing.Use the Dat
 a Management Planning (DMP) Tool to organize research projects.Apply funda
 mental data management strategies during the active execution phase of res
 earch.Protect sensitive or personal data if collected during researchDisti
 nguish between working data storage and open data repositories (platforms 
 used for sharing and archiving final data).Locate the appropriate data rep
 ository for your specific discipline or project.Explain the broader import
 ance of data reproducibility in the research ecosystem.Identify campus res
 ources available for data support\, including the DataLab\, Research Data 
 Management (RDM) Team\, and the Clinical and Translational Science Center 
 (CTSC).\nNo previous experience is required. All disciplines are welcome.\
 n\n\nPlease register for the Zoom link.\n\nThis six-workshop series is a c
 ollaboration between the library's Scholarly Communications Program\, the 
 Researcher Services department\, and Blaisdell Medical Library. For any qu
 estions\, please contact the Scholarly Communication Officer Michael Ladis
 ch (mladisch@ucdavis.edu). Check our events calendar for more publishing w
 orkshops.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/navigating-data-management-fo
 r-publication
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
