BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ucdavis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/covered-faculty-author-talks-by-claire-goldstein-and-michael-dylan-foster"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:Covered: Faculty Author Talks by Claire Goldstein and Michael Dyla
 n Foster
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260513T003000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260513T023000
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51817344074825
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening with UC Davis faculty authors Claire Go
 ldstein and Michael Dylan Foster as part of Covered\, a monthly event seri
 es celebrating recent books from the College of Letters and Science.\n \n\
 nClaire Goldstein\, professor of French and Italian\, discusses In the Sun
  King’s Cosmos\, her engaging study of how comets shaped scientific\, po
 litical and cultural imagination in 17th century France. \n Michael Dylan 
 Foster\, professor of East Asian Languages and Cultures\, presents the exp
 anded edition of The Book of Yokai\, exploring the folklore\, history and 
 ongoing cultural life of Japan’s supernatural beings. \n\n\n\n \n\nCover
 ed: Spotlighting Faculty Authors in Letters and Science is co-sponsored by
  the Jan Shrem and Maria Manetti Shrem Museum and the UC Davis Library.
LOCATION:Manetti Shrem Museum
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/covered-faculty-author-talks-
 by-claire-goldstein-and-michael-dylan-foster
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
